            <fr:title text="Classification of formally real Jordan algebras">Classification of formally real Jordan algebras</fr:title>
            <fr:meta name="source">
              <fr:link href="/baez-2002-octonions/" title="The Octonions" uri="http://localhost:8000/baez-2002-octonions/" display-uri="baez-2002-octonions" type="local">[baez-2002-octonions]</fr:link>
            </fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>There are four infinite families of formally real Jordan algebras and one exception:</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li>The algebra <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {H}(n,\mathbb {R})]]></fr:tex> with the Jordan product</html:li>
<html:li>The algebra <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {H}(n,\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex> with the Jordan product</html:li>
<html:li>The algebra <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {H}(n,\mathbb {H})]]></fr:tex> with the Jordan product</html:li>
<html:li>The <html:dfn>Spin Factor</html:dfn> algebra <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^{n}\oplus \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> with the product <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(v,\alpha )\circ (w,\beta )=(\alpha  w+\beta  v, \langle  v,w\rangle  + \alpha \beta )]]></fr:tex></html:li>
<html:li>The <html:dfn>Exceptional Jordan algebra</html:dfn> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathfrak {H}(3,\mathbb {O})]]></fr:tex> with the Jordan product</html:li></html:ol>
            <html:p>(See section 3 of John Baez's <fr:link href="/baez-2002-octonions/" title="The Octonions" uri="http://localhost:8000/baez-2002-octonions/" display-uri="baez-2002-octonions" type="local">The Octonions</fr:link>, page 20 of the PDF.)</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
